text: JAW-DROPPING FIREWORKS: New York Rings in 2026 at Times Square | AQ1BThousands of revelers packed Times Square as New York welcomed 2026 with the iconic New Year’s Eve ball drop at midnight. Despite tight security and freezing temperatures, crowds cheered as fireworks lit up the skyline, marking one of the world’s most-watched celebrations. The event symbolized hope, renewal, and global unity. For more details, watch our story and subscribe to our channel, DRM News. Cities worldwide celebrate the arrival of 2026 with spectacular fireworks and light shows, from Taipei 101 to London's Thames.
